HEADWORD: Brittle
<hw>Brit"tle</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>britel</ets>, <ets>brutel</ets>, AS. <ets>bryttian</ets> to
dispense, fr. <ets>bre⟦oacute⟧tan</ets> to break; akin to Icel.
<ets>brytja</ets>, Sw. <ets>bryta</ets>, Dan. <ets>bryde</ets>. Cf.
<er>Brickle</er>.]</ety> <def>Easily broken; apt to break; fragile; not
tough or tenacious<-- contrast to flexible; usually hard -->.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Farewell, thou pretty, <qex>brittle</qex> piece⟦br⟧
